undances. The quadrupole spectrum shape changes very little from RHIC to LHC\nenergies. Taken in combination those characteristics strongly suggest a unique\n{\\em nonflow} (and nonjet) QCD mechanism for the NJ quadrupole conventionally\nrepresented by $v_2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 25 Sep 2016 02:42:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-26"}
