and Ni II. Our study indicates that EEs occurring in\nactive regions have mostly upper-chromosphere/transition-region origin. We\nsuggest that magnetic reconnection resulting from the braidings of small-scale\ntransition region loops is one of the possible mechanisms of energy release\nthat are responsible for the EEs reported in this paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 25 Sep 2016 04:12:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-15"}
